definitions: writing on top of other writing

examples.text: there should not be any overwriting on the form

definitions: the destruction or loss of data by entering new data in its place

examples.text: each new file has a unique name to avoid inadvertent overwriting

shortDefinitions: destruction of data by replacing with new data

definitions: the action or process of writing too elaborately or ornately

examples.text: he tells his story simply despite occasional overwriting

definitions: (in insurance) the acceptance of more risk than the premium income limits allow

examples.text: the members may be required to make available additional funds to cover the overwriting
